social_posts.post_text: First Nutcracker gig in the books. Thank you @pacificfestivalballet for having me. Looking forward to next year!
Happy Birthday Mr. Balanchine. It’s truly a gift to dance your ballets.
Looking forward to dancing Fancy Free again on February 5th at 3:00 pm. ⚓️💪🏽

Happy Ballet Day y’all🫡
#maledancer #newyorkcityballet #ballet

Spent the week flying blue bird style! 🦅
4 in one week and 2 more to go💪🏽

Finally made it in a book! So excited to be a part of #movementatthestillpoint photographed by @markmannphoto 
Get your copy at @rizzolibooks

Gold Variation from the Jewels Pas de Quatre in Sleeping Beauty.

It’s been a long but very fulfilling winter season. Happy to close it out tomorrow with one more blue bird tomorrow at 3pm.

Just wanted to say thank you for all the love and support from everyone. Still can’t quite believe that I’m now a principal dancer with @nycballet ( I’ve been pinching myself for the past 12 hours haha). This is something I’ve always wanted for as long as I can remember and I’m truly looking forward to everything that is to come. 
Thank you ❤️

Off to London today! Looking forward to performing in @tilerpeck ‘s show Turn It Out with Tiler Peck and Friends. We will be performing at @sadlers_wells March 9th - 11th. If you are in the area make sure to come on by!!!! 
Excited to revisit Alonzo King’s Swift Arrow @linesballet

Enjoying the last day here in NYC before we head to Madrid tomorrow! Little gym day to stay feeling strong and healthy with @roman.julian.mejia 

#balletdancers#balletfitness#gym#gymmotivation#newyorkcityballet

Making new friends in Italy. When @adamzhanbaktiyar suggests a turning competition and you start to sweat, but then it just so happens to go okay😅

Had a blast in Bologna! Thank you @daniele_cipriani_entertainment for having me. It was truly inspiring to be surrounded by such an amazing group of artists🙌🏼
Always great to revisit Tchaikovsky pas de deux and had a great time debuting @wheeldony ‘s This Bitter Earth.
Until the next time 🇮🇹❤️

Performed my last show of @alexeiratmansky ‘s Namouna yesterday. Definitely one of the most fun and challenging ballets I’ve had the privilege to dance on stage! I have so many favorite moments from this marathon of a ballet but I’ll leave you with two because other wise you’ll be scrolling for a while haha.
Thank you @ashleylaracey for being such a trusting partner and congratulations @georgina_pazcoguin on a legendary career.
